<!-- ============== PROGRAM & EVENT GUIDE ============== -->
<section class="lyg-section lyg-guide" id="lyg-guide" aria-labelledby="lyg-h2-guide">
  <div class="lyg-wrap">
    <div class="lyg-h2-wrap">
      <span class="lyg-eyebrow">Reference</span>
      <h2 id="lyg-h2-guide">Program &amp; event guide</h2>
      <p>Full descriptions of every group, event, and resource.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="lyg-guide__list">
      <details id="guide-junior"><summary>Junior Group (Ages 5&ndash;10)</summary><div class="lyg-guide__body"><p>Junior group is for LGBTQIA+ youth between the ages of 5-10 and their caregivers. This group creates a welcoming space for youth and their family members to explore their identities, make friends, and build a supportive community. Adult mentors help bridge the gap between the newly identifying LGBTQIA+ young people and their families by providing insight, wisdom, and resources in a fun and engaging environment.</p></div></details>

      <details id="guide-tween"><summary>Tween Group (Ages 11&ndash;13)</summary><div class="lyg-guide__body"><p>Tween group is for LGBTQIA+ youth between the ages of 11-13. This group creates a welcoming space for youth to explore their identities, make friends, and build self-esteem with a supportive community. This group is driven by the needs and suggestions of the youth involved, and facilitated by Adult Mentors. Activities &amp; Topics Include: Arts &amp; Crafts, Social and Emotional Development, Games, Identity Exploration, Healthy Relationships, and Comprehensive Health Education (just to name a few!)</p></div></details>

      <details id="guide-teen"><summary>Teen Group (Ages 14&ndash;18)</summary><div class="lyg-guide__body"><p>Teen Group brings together LGBTQIA+ youth between the ages of 14-18 in an affirming, fun and relaxing setting. Youth have the opportunity to explore their gender and sexuality, build self-worth and healthy relationships, and connect with the broader LGBTQIA+ community. This group is driven by the needs and suggestions of the youth involved, and facilitated by Adult Mentors and members of our Youth Leadership Council. Activities &amp; Topics Include: Game night, Queer History, Arts &amp; Crafts, Mental Health First-aid, Gender Expression &amp; Euphoria, Healthy Relationships and Comprehensive Health Education (just to name a few!)</p></div></details>

      <details id="guide-rising"><summary>LYG Rising (Ages 18&ndash;24)</summary><div class="lyg-guide__body"><p>LYG Rising is a monthly meetup for LGBTQIA+ Young Adults (ages 18-24) to socialize, learn life skills, and to develop the tools needed to build community and act as agents of change.</p></div></details>

      <details id="guide-melanin"><summary>Melanin MagiQ (Ages 13&ndash;19)</summary><div class="lyg-guide__body"><p>Melanin MagiQ is a group for LGBTQIA2S+ Youth of the Global Majority - This group is specifically for Black, Indigenous, Latin&eacute;, Asian, Multi-Racial, and other Melanated youth, and is led by Mentors who also represent these racial &amp; ethnic identities. The Melanin MagiQ group provides a brave and affirming space for young people to discuss the unique ways that their identities intersect, build self-worth and healthy relationships, and grow into joyful and connected young adults.</p></div></details>

      <details id="guide-tnbi"><summary>Trans, Non-Binary &amp; Intersex Group (Ages 13&ndash;19)</summary><div class="lyg-guide__body"><p>Trans, Non-Binary, and Intersex Group is focused on the social, emotional, legal, and medical needs of gender expansive teens. Trans and NonBinary mentors provide support and help guide youth through the complexities of their own self-discovery and the practical steps toward realizing and affirming their gender identity and expression.</p></div></details>

      <details id="guide-ylc"><summary>Youth Leadership Council</summary><div class="lyg-guide__body"><p>Our Youth Leadership Council (YLC) provides an opportunity to develop advocacy and leadership skills through collaborative organizing, peer education and support, and community service. The YLC serves as the guiding youth voice and vision for all of LYG's programs and events, and works closely with LYG staff and adult mentors to keep the needs of our youth centered.</p><p>Council members must be at least 13 years old, and are selected through an application process. For more information or to apply, please email our <a href="mailto:programs@louisvilleyouthgroup.org"><strong>Program Team</strong></a>.</p></div></details>

      <details id="guide-bl"><summary>Beyond Labels &amp; Resource Closet</summary><div class="lyg-guide__body"><p>Beyond Labels is our free Resource Closet, open to youth during all of our programming. Stop by to pick up free clothing and gender-affirming items &mdash; no cost, no questions, and no need to explain yourself. We want every young person to be able to show up as their fullest self.</p><p>Available items include binder fittings, trans tape, gaffs, wigs, cosmetics, and more. If there's something you need that you don't see, just ask a staff member or mentor &mdash; we'll do our best to help.</p></div></details>

      <details id="guide-prom"><summary>Pride Prom + Lavender Graduation (Spring)</summary><div class="lyg-guide__body"><p>We provide a safe and celebratory space for LGBTQIA+ and allied youth (ages 14-24) to enjoy a fun evening with friends, old and new. During our prom, we hold a graduation ceremony to affirm and uplift our students who are graduating from home schooling, NTI, GED programs, trade school, traditional high school, and undergraduate programs.</p></div></details>

      <details id="guide-camp"><summary>Youth Empowerment Camp (Fall)</summary><div class="lyg-guide__body"><p>LYG Camp is a fun weekend to socialize, develop leadership skills, and enjoy nature. Activities include campfires, night hikes, challenge course initiatives, and lots of lively conversation.</p></div></details>

      <details id="guide-nye"><summary>New Year's Eve Lock-In (Winter)</summary><div class="lyg-guide__body"><p>LYG provides a safe and sober over-night event for youth to celebrate the New Year. Activities include board games, video games, movies, arts &amp; crafts, a new year ritual, and sparkling cider at midnight. Dinner, Dessert, and Breakfast are provided.</p></div></details>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<script>
(function () {
  var root = document.getElementById('lyg-programs-root');
  if (!root) return;
  var hero = root.querySelector('[data-lyg-hero]');
  if (!hero) return;
  var slides = Array.prototype.slice.call(hero.querySelectorAll('.lyg-hero__slide'));
  var dots = Array.prototype.slice.call(hero.querySelectorAll('[data-lyg-dot]'));
  var prev = hero.querySelector('[data-lyg-prev]');
  var next = hero.querySelector('[data-lyg-next]');
  var i = 0, timer = null;
  var reduce = window.matchMedia && window.matchMedia('(prefers-reduced-motion: reduce)').matches;

  function show(n) {
    i = (n + slides.length) % slides.length;
    slides.forEach(function (s, idx) { s.classList.toggle('is-active', idx === i); });
    dots.forEach(function (d, idx) { d.classList.toggle('is-active', idx === i); });
  }
  function start() {
    if (reduce || slides.length < 2) return;
    stop();
    timer = setInterval(function () { show(i + 1); }, 6000);
  }
  function stop() { if (timer) { clearInterval(timer); timer = null; } }

  if (prev) prev.addEventListener('click', function () { show(i - 1); start(); });
  if (next) next.addEventListener('click', function () { show(i + 1); start(); });
  dots.forEach(function (d, idx) { d.addEventListener('click', function () { show(idx); start(); }); });
  hero.addEventListener('mouseenter', stop);
  hero.addEventListener('mouseleave', start);

  show(0);
  start();
})();
</script>

